race.comment: UNLIMITED SPENDING (3) improved last start to finish second over 1609m at Saratoga after being in contention on the bend. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. SNIDE (15) finished second, beaten 0.8 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1308m at this track (Dirt) after she was in contention on the corner. Meeting a deeper field this time but she cannot be underestimated. NEW ATTITUDE (1) has been in the betting recently but hasn't managed to live up to market expectations. Most recently finished fourth over 1106m at Saratoga (Dirt), beaten 17 lengths. Right in the mix. PRIVATE PROPERTY (12) returned from a spell a week-and-a-half ago when she was beaten 7 lengths into seventh over 1609m at this track. Strips fitter and should be thereabouts. Something for the Multiples: BOLT HOUSE (7)
